Quote:  [South Island Kiwi] Like many of the New Zealand birds the  apteryx is nocturnal in its habits, dwelling beneath extensive beds of fern, where it conceals itself during the day. The largest species, the `fireman' of the whalers, is from the Middle Island, and is considerably larger than

the other two.
